{"cursor":"31158","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"In linguistics, a 'compound' is a lexeme (less precisely, a word) that consists\nof more than one stem. 'Compounding' or 'composition' is the process of word\nformation that creates compound lexemes (the other word-formation process being\nderivation). That is, in familiar terms, compounding occurs when two or more\nwords are joined together to make them one word. The meaning of the compound may\nbe very different from the meanings of its components in isolation.\n","linknr":318,"url":"Compound_(linguistics)","recorded":1362503604,"links":47,"instances":["linguistics","linguistics","linguistics","linguistics"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Linguistics","Word coinage","Linguistic morphology"],"headings":["Formation of compounds","Subclasses","Examples from different languages","Recent trends","Compounding by language","See also","Notes","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg/20px-Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c1/Abwasserbehandlungsanlage.jpg/250px-Abwasserbehandlungsanlage.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Wiktionary-logo-en.svg/37px-Wiktionary-logo-en.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["derivation","linguistics"],["incorporation","linguistics"],["incorporation","linguistics"],["stem","linguistics"],["internationalism","linguistics"],["incorporation","linguistics"]],"members":["incorporation","stem","derivation","internationalism"],"related":["Linguistics","Lexeme","Word","Wo